patches./Deployment-redis-slave.yaml:
apiVersion: extensions/v1beta1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  labels:
    app: redis
    chart: redis-5.0.0
    heritage: Tiller
    release: redis
  name: redis-slave
spec:
  template:
    metadata:
      annotations:
        checksum/secret: FORKED_CHECKSUM
    spec:
      $setElementOrder/containers:
      - name: redis
      containers:
      - livenessProbe:
          failureThreshold: HI_IM_FORKED
        name: redis
patches./Secret-redis.yaml:
apiVersion: v1
data:
  redis-password: IM_A_PASSWORD
kind: Secret
metadata:
  labels:
    app: redis
    chart: redis-5.0.0
    heritage: Tiller
    release: redis
  name: redis
patches./StatefulSet-redis-master.yaml:
apiVersion: apps/v1beta2
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  labels:
    app: redis
    chart: redis-5.0.0
    heritage: Tiller
    release: redis
  name: redis-master
spec:
  template:
    metadata:
      annotations:
        checksum/secret: 7d8062c935157159cd0e3392280371c8cca1f35ccc16548d3f806c4ce09764ee
    spec:
      $setElementOrder/initContainers:
      - name: volume-permissions
      initContainers:
      - imagePullPolicy: HELLO_IM_FORKED
        name: volume-permissions

metadata.name: redis
metadata.releaseNotes:
[stable/redis] support redis docker library image (#7745)

* refactor(stable/redis): support redis docker library image

BREAKING CHANGES:
- `master.args` and `slave.args` are removed. Use `master.command` or
  `slave.command` instead in order to override the image entrypoint,
   or `master.extraFlags` to pass additional flags to `redis-server`.
- `disableCommands` is now interpreted as an array of strings instead
   of a string of comma separated values.
- `master.persistence.path` now defaults to `/data`.

Signed-off-by: Jacob LeGrone <git@jacob.work>

* test(stable/redis): add ci values for base images & configurations
